WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:00.959 --> 00:00:02.334
<i>I have thousands of greybeards.</i>

2
00:00:02.335 --> 00:00:05.171
If your greybeards can fight.
the Queen will have them.

3
00:00:05.672 --> 00:00:07.090
They will fight hard.

4
00:00:07.799 --> 00:00:09.009
like northerners.

5
00:00:13.763 --> 00:00:17.141
Our victory depends on
the efforts of the small folk.

6
00:00:17.142 --> 00:00:19.644
The King has promised us
some relief.

7
00:00:20.353 --> 00:00:21.438
Did he say when?

8
00:00:22.480 --> 00:00:24.402
I've decided
to send Joffrey to ward

9
00:00:24.482 --> 00:00:26.860
<i>with my cousin.
Lady Jeyne Arryn.</i>

10
00:00:27.027 --> 00:00:28.987
<i>Aegon and Viserys
will accompany him.</i>

11
00:00:29.487 --> 00:00:31.990
I need you to be the mother
to them that I cannot.

12
00:00:32.198 --> 00:00:34.492
<i>Guard them
as a dragon guards her eggs.</i>

13
00:00:35.493 --> 00:00:39.164
Do you accept me
as your Queen and ruler?

14
00:00:39.456 --> 00:00:41.665
<i>Or do you cling even now
to what you think you lost?</i>

15
00:00:41.666 --> 00:00:44.210
<i>You've come here
after quarreling with your wife.</i>

16
00:00:45.337 --> 00:00:48.297
I mean. does it please you
that her legitimacy is contested

17
00:00:48.298 --> 00:00:51.509
<i>as you stand here with a castle
and a dragon?</i>

18
00:00:51.801 --> 00:00:54.401
Ser Willem Blackwood
of House Blackwood. Your Grace.

19
00:00:54.512 --> 00:00:55.971
Once you and your dragon

20
00:00:55.972 --> 00:00:58.350
bring the Queen's justice
to the Brackens.

21
00:00:58.808 --> 00:01:00.185
our armies will be yours.

22
00:01:01.561 --> 00:01:03.396
<i>Cole is already
preparing his attack.</i>

23
00:01:03.813 --> 00:01:06.733
<i>The two
of you have been plotting</i>

24
00:01:06.858 --> 00:01:08.485
without my authority.

25
00:01:08.860 --> 00:01:10.028
<i>They don't care what I think.</i>

26
00:01:10.403 --> 00:01:11.987
Do you think
simply wearing the crown

27
00:01:11.988 --> 00:01:13.239
imbues you with wisdom?

28
00:01:16.868 --> 00:01:18.703
Cole marches on Rook's Rest.

29
00:01:18.995 --> 00:01:20.330
- Send me.
- No.

30
00:01:20.705 --> 00:01:23.667
<i>You must send me. Your Grace.</i>

31
00:01:23.917 --> 00:01:25.710
This was your secret plot. Cole?

32
00:01:26.002 --> 00:01:27.420
<i>For the King himself
to lay ambush</i>

33
00:01:27.545 --> 00:01:29.171
<i>and mayhaps die in the attempt.</i>

34
00:01:29.172 --> 00:01:30.340
No!

35
00:01:32.384 --> 00:01:33.593
Thank the gods!

36
00:01:34.219 --> 00:01:35.428
<i>Dracarys!</i>

37
00:01:36.262 --> 00:01:37.389
No!

38
00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:45.074
Free Gift Cards and Tech Items with
Southwest Points: www.fairylandshop.me

39
00:01:46.773 --> 00:01:47.893
<i>Where is His Grace?</i>

40
00:05:07.098 --> 00:05:09.809
- Only one.
- That's enough. stand back.

41
00:05:16.775 --> 00:05:18.276
Behold!

42
00:05:18.902 --> 00:05:21.946
The traitor dragon Meleys!

43
00:05:22.072 --> 00:05:26.241
Slain at Rook's Rest

44
00:05:26.242 --> 00:05:27.952
by your king!

45
00:05:30.121 --> 00:05:31.580
To Aegon!

46
00:05:40.090 --> 00:05:43.301
- It can't be...
- They killed a dragon!

47
00:05:43.426 --> 00:05:46.429
Mark my
words. this is a black omen.

48
00:06:04.155 --> 00:06:06.825
Rhaenyra will answer this.

49
00:06:07.659 --> 00:06:09.327
'Tis an abomination.

50
00:06:10.495 --> 00:06:12.872
Don't they realize
we won the battle?

51
00:06:13.707 --> 00:06:15.959
Strange victory...

52
00:06:16.668 --> 00:06:18.335
if it was one.

53
00:06:35.562 --> 00:06:37.981
Behold!

54
00:06:39.024 --> 00:06:41.817
The traitor dragon Meleys!

55
00:06:41.818 --> 00:06:43.652
I thought the dragons was gods.

56
00:06:43.653 --> 00:06:47.197
Slain at Rook's
Rest by your king!

57
00:06:55.540 --> 00:06:57.208
It's just meat.

58
00:09:16.806 --> 00:09:17.891
Is he alive?

59
00:09:18.016 --> 00:09:20.018
His Grace...

60
00:09:20.143 --> 00:09:23.063
remains with us. for the moment.

61
00:10:19.786 --> 00:10:21.036
Is my son going to die?

62
00:10:21.037 --> 00:10:22.872
I'm afraid I cannot say.

63
00:10:23.123 --> 00:10:26.542
Now. if you'll excuse me. Your
Grace. these next hours are most critical.

64
00:10:26.543 --> 00:10:27.752
Of course.

65
00:10:40.807 --> 00:10:42.434
Easy as you can.

66
00:11:02.287 --> 00:11:05.415
Someone will have
to rule in his stead.

67
00:11:28.605 --> 00:11:31.273
- What happened?
- We took the castle.

68
00:11:31.274 --> 00:11:34.027
At the cost of some 900 men.

69
00:11:35.695 --> 00:11:37.447
So I've heard.

70
00:11:39.032 --> 00:11:41.701
I left a meager garrison
behind to protect it

71
00:11:41.826 --> 00:11:44.329
and the king's dragon.

72
00:11:44.454 --> 00:11:46.498
Sunfyrewas long in the dying.

73
00:11:46.623 --> 00:11:49.334
The king. Ser Criston.
what befell him?

74
00:11:52.879 --> 00:11:55.548
His Grace fought valiantly.

75
00:12:01.680 --> 00:12:02.889
And Aemond?

76
00:12:10.021 --> 00:12:12.190
What was his part in this?

77
00:12:15.860 --> 00:12:18.029
I could not say.

78
00:12:21.491 --> 00:12:25.203
Our largest
dragon has been killed.

79
00:12:25.328 --> 00:12:29.708
Criston Cole marches about
the Crownlands unchallenged.

80
00:12:30.166 --> 00:12:33.336
Duskendale and
Rook's Rest are gone.

81
00:12:34.379 --> 00:12:36.005
We still have no ground army

82
00:12:36.006 --> 00:12:39.008
but the one we hope
that Daemon will raise.

83
00:12:39.009 --> 00:12:43.178
He who has left us...
after some marital spat.

84
00:12:45.056 --> 00:12:47.392
Do you take issue
with me. Ser Alfred?

85
00:12:49.936 --> 00:12:52.105
My loyalty to you is
proven. my queen.

86
00:12:52.230 --> 00:12:54.356
Your loyalty. perhaps.

87
00:12:54.357 --> 00:12:57.192
but your willingness to give
me deference in a time of war.

88
00:12:57.193 --> 00:13:00.362
I could never doubt
your capability.

89
00:13:00.363 --> 00:13:03.283
or your quickness of mind.

90
00:13:04.409 --> 00:13:06.368
It is merely that
the gentler sex.

91
00:13:06.369 --> 00:13:08.788
heretofore. has
not been much privy

92
00:13:08.913 --> 00:13:11.749
to the strategies of battle.

93
00:13:11.750 --> 00:13:13.710
or their execution.

94
00:13:15.253 --> 00:13:17.046
There has been
peace in our lifetime.

95
00:13:17.047 --> 00:13:19.591
You've seen no more
battles than I have.

96
00:13:39.319 --> 00:13:41.945
Send to Maidenpool
and to Crackclaw Point.

97
00:13:41.946 --> 00:13:43.113
Let them man their garrisons

98
00:13:43.114 --> 00:13:44.740
and give them stores or weapons

99
00:13:44.741 --> 00:13:46.284
if they find them wanting.

100
00:13:47.285 --> 00:13:48.786
If Cole pursues his campaign.

101
00:13:48.787 --> 00:13:52.081
- our allies must be ready.
- We must answer Rook's Rest.

102
00:13:52.082 --> 00:13:54.416
- and Duskendale.
- They are lost already.

103
00:13:54.417 --> 00:13:56.960
But Vhagar is
depleted after such

104
00:13:56.961 --> 00:13:58.129
a hard-fought battle.

105
00:13:58.254 --> 00:13:59.421
If Aegon is dead...

106
00:13:59.422 --> 00:14:00.798
We will soon know it.

107
00:14:00.799 --> 00:14:02.758
'Twould
be a victory in name only.

108
00:14:02.759 --> 00:14:04.927
They will soon prop
up another in his stead.

109
00:14:04.928 --> 00:14:06.137
The time is ripe.

110
00:14:06.262 --> 00:14:07.502
If we can strike King's Landing

111
00:14:07.597 --> 00:14:09.098
before their dragon
is recovered...

112
00:14:09.099 --> 00:14:10.642
Then I myself must do it.

113
00:14:10.767 --> 00:14:14.311
My queen. you are the
crown. It is out of the question.

114
00:14:14.312 --> 00:14:16.939
What would you have me do?

115
00:14:37.460 --> 00:14:39.546
Jace?

116
00:14:41.840 --> 00:14:43.466
Where are you going?

117
00:14:44.676 --> 00:14:48.971
To Harrenhal. To
treat with Daemon.

118
00:14:48.972 --> 00:14:50.347
Rhaenys is fallen.

119
00:14:50.348 --> 00:14:52.225
He must affirm his
loyalty to my mother

120
00:14:52.350 --> 00:14:54.352
and report his standing.

121
00:14:57.063 --> 00:14:59.357
And you think
you will tame him...

122
00:14:59.482 --> 00:15:01.067
when the queen
herself could not?

123
00:15:01.192 --> 00:15:03.986
My mother gladly sends you away

124
00:15:03.987 --> 00:15:05.821
to scout. to fight.

125
00:15:05.822 --> 00:15:08.908
whilst I'm here being forced
to play the coddled princeling.

126
00:15:09.034 --> 00:15:13.246
- It's humiliating. Baela.
- She only protects you.

127
00:15:13.371 --> 00:15:14.706
You are the succession.

128
00:15:14.831 --> 00:15:18.877
Then I must be seen to
act for her claim and mine.

129
00:15:22.589 --> 00:15:25.258
I can sit still no longer.

130
00:15:27.761 --> 00:15:29.387
I must act.

131
00:15:36.895 --> 00:15:38.396
The Freys.

132
00:15:40.398 --> 00:15:42.733
They control the
crossing at the Twins.

133
00:15:42.734 --> 00:15:45.569
Cregan Stark's graybeards
are marching south.

134
00:15:45.570 --> 00:15:48.906
If his men had a direct
route into the Riverlands.

135
00:15:48.907 --> 00:15:51.034
we would not have to
wait for Daemon to act.

136
00:15:51.743 --> 00:15:54.412
I will treat with The
Freys to secure it.

137
00:15:54.537 --> 00:15:56.247
She will not like it.

138
00:15:56.748 --> 00:16:00.627
Then don't tell her.
Not until I'm away.

139
00:16:13.807 --> 00:16:16.935
The hour
is late and my dragon is hungry.

140
00:16:17.060 --> 00:16:20.396
- You
have no choice but to submit.

141
00:16:20.397 --> 00:16:22.272
Our terms are
simple. Lord Bracken.

142
00:16:22.273 --> 00:16:25.985
Renounce the false
king Aegon as a usurper

143
00:16:26.111 --> 00:16:28.780
and bend the knee to me

144
00:16:28.905 --> 00:16:30.572
or your house burns.

145
00:16:30.573 --> 00:16:33.618
I would sooner be the
Lord of Bones and Cinders

146
00:16:33.743 --> 00:16:38.080
than bend my knee before
some heathen Blackwood cunt...

147
00:16:38.081 --> 00:16:39.666
and his hired dragon.

148
00:16:39.791 --> 00:16:41.292
The Brackens were
a people hatched out

149
00:16:41.418 --> 00:16:43.752
of the deepest of the
Seven Hells. Your Grace.

150
00:16:43.753 --> 00:16:45.295
It would be a
kindness to oblige them

151
00:16:45.296 --> 00:16:47.297
and send them back
whence they came.

152
00:16:47.298 --> 00:16:48.590
Did your brother's head

153
00:16:48.591 --> 00:16:51.136
keep on its way
back to you. Willem?

154
00:16:51.469 --> 00:16:53.346
I heard the maggots got to it.

155
00:16:53.471 --> 00:16:56.474
That is quite the
impression. Lord Bracken.

156
00:16:57.308 --> 00:16:59.519
But alas. not an answer.

157
00:17:09.195 --> 00:17:11.531
We choose fire.

158
00:17:21.374 --> 00:17:24.794
I did not think they
would be so eager to die.

159
00:17:25.503 --> 00:17:27.380
They made their choice.

160
00:17:27.672 --> 00:17:30.674
- You should've indulged them.
- I need them alive.

161
00:17:30.675 --> 00:17:33.636
I came here to raise
swords. not corpses.

162
00:17:34.179 --> 00:17:37.348
But now you see what my
house has known for generations.

163
00:17:37.349 --> 00:17:39.351
They are pigheaded.
intransigent...

164
00:17:39.476 --> 00:17:42.020
They would rather
burn than succumb.

165
00:17:45.690 --> 00:17:47.859
Exactly the kind of men I need.

166
00:17:49.861 --> 00:17:51.362
It may yet be possible. I think.

167
00:17:51.363 --> 00:17:53.406
for both of us to
achieve our ends.

168
00:17:53.531 --> 00:17:56.200
We have fought them
for an age and more.

169
00:17:56.201 --> 00:17:57.659
Then perhaps you could try

170
00:17:57.660 --> 00:18:00.038
less fighting and more...

171
00:18:03.833 --> 00:18:05.585
persuading.

172
00:18:06.378 --> 00:18:09.089
They are unyielding in battle.

173
00:18:15.845 --> 00:18:18.681
But every man has a weakness.

174
00:18:18.682 --> 00:18:21.184
You take my meaning. then.

175
00:18:24.729 --> 00:18:28.900
There are things the crown
itself must not been seen to do.

176
00:18:30.235 --> 00:18:31.736
Show them your worst.

177
00:18:31.861 --> 00:18:34.196
I am your servant. Your Grace.

178
00:18:55.260 --> 00:18:58.929
<i>Over the
centuries. many and more armies</i>

179
00:18:58.930 --> 00:19:02.225
have broken themselves
against my bloody gate.

180
00:19:06.438 --> 00:19:08.606
Are you listening?

181
00:19:09.399 --> 00:19:10.775
My lady.

182
00:19:11.276 --> 00:19:13.945
The Eyrie itself is impregnable.

183
00:19:16.114 --> 00:19:19.451
Unless. of course. we're
descended upon from the sky.

184
00:19:19.576 --> 00:19:22.244
You promised the Queen
Rhaenyra 15.000 swords...

185
00:19:22.245 --> 00:19:25.498
In return for
protection. A dragon.

186
00:19:27.000 --> 00:19:29.836
Then she has
exceeded your terms.

187
00:19:29.961 --> 00:19:31.129
She sent two.

188
00:19:31.671 --> 00:19:34.174
Both still wet from the egg.

189
00:19:35.800 --> 00:19:38.345
I have hunting hounds
that are more fearsome.

190
00:19:38.470 --> 00:19:40.805
They are dragons nonetheless.

191
00:19:41.306 --> 00:19:42.598
I do not recall you specifying

192
00:19:42.599 --> 00:19:44.309
the size of the
beast in your request.

193
00:19:44.434 --> 00:19:46.311
Will you goad me. child?

194
00:19:46.811 --> 00:19:49.814
When your bread and shelter
now depend on my pleasure?

195
00:19:51.483 --> 00:19:53.526
The dragons will grow...

196
00:19:54.486 --> 00:19:56.696
- in time.
- I don't have time.

197
00:19:58.448 --> 00:20:00.825
I mislike feeling powerless.

198
00:20:02.160 --> 00:20:03.661
So do I.

199
00:20:10.168 --> 00:20:11.960
This will be your chamber.

200
00:20:11.961 --> 00:20:14.172
I'll expect you at
supper this evening?

201
00:20:17.133 --> 00:20:21.346
My sympathies for the
death of your grandmother.

202
00:20:29.521 --> 00:20:32.314
The way they spoke at
my small council today.

203
00:20:32.315 --> 00:20:35.818
Do they hold you
responsible for Rhaenys and her dragon?

204
00:20:35.819 --> 00:20:37.529
I would rather they had.

205
00:20:38.029 --> 00:20:40.740
They speak around me. not to me.

206
00:20:41.408 --> 00:20:42.579
They would
make me queen.

207
00:20:42.659 --> 00:20:44.827
but they wish to keep
me here. confined.

208
00:20:44.828 --> 00:20:47.372
They betray their own smallness.

209
00:20:47.914 --> 00:20:49.207
In truth. I cannot fault them.

210
00:20:49.332 --> 00:20:53.502
I am now the sovereign.
I cannot do as I please.

211
00:20:53.503 --> 00:20:56.213
And war has ever
been for men to make.

212
00:20:56.214 --> 00:20:59.717
You are your father's
chosen successor.

213
00:20:59.718 --> 00:21:02.177
He did not prepare me to fight.

214
00:21:02.178 --> 00:21:04.055
If I had been a son.

215
00:21:04.180 --> 00:21:07.726
a sword thrust into my hand
the moment I could walk.

216
00:21:08.226 --> 00:21:10.520
Instead. I was given
my father's cup...

217
00:21:11.062 --> 00:21:13.606
taught the name of
every lord and castle

218
00:21:13.732 --> 00:21:15.190
between Storm's
End and the Twins.

219
00:21:15.191 --> 00:21:18.403
but not the difference
between hilt and foible.

220
00:21:19.279 --> 00:21:21.072
And they know it.

221
00:21:22.407 --> 00:21:26.035
- And Daemon as well... - Shall your
evening meal be served here. Your Grace?

222
00:21:26.036 --> 00:21:27.746
Not now.

223
00:21:33.585 --> 00:21:35.295
Will you send to him?

224
00:21:36.713 --> 00:21:39.548
For too long. I have
looked to him for strength.

225
00:21:39.549 --> 00:21:41.634
If I must be supplicant
to my own husband.

226
00:21:41.760 --> 00:21:43.595
what does that make me?

227
00:21:46.931 --> 00:21:50.143
I do not know my part. Mysaria.

228
00:21:52.979 --> 00:21:55.940
The path I walk
has never been trod.

229
00:21:56.941 --> 00:22:00.737
Criston Cole made a mistake.

230
00:22:02.113 --> 00:22:06.408
Parading a dragon's head through
the streets like a prize of war.

231
00:22:06.409 --> 00:22:08.452
but the people see an ill omen.

232
00:22:08.453 --> 00:22:09.953
Yes. as do I.

233
00:22:09.954 --> 00:22:13.290
They are afraid.
bread is scarce.

234
00:22:13.291 --> 00:22:14.750
the king has fallen.

235
00:22:14.751 --> 00:22:17.337
they whisper to each other
that when Viserys lived.

236
00:22:17.462 --> 00:22:19.588
there was peace.

237
00:22:19.589 --> 00:22:22.342
But will whispers
tear down stone...

238
00:22:22.467 --> 00:22:23.843
or break shields?

239
00:22:23.968 --> 00:22:27.347
Do not underestimate
your subjects.

240
00:22:27.472 --> 00:22:28.973
They are a thousand-thousand

241
00:22:29.099 --> 00:22:30.766
living in the shadow
of the Red Keep

242
00:22:30.767 --> 00:22:33.311
and forgotten for too long.

243
00:22:33.978 --> 00:22:36.189
And you think
they will turn to me.

244
00:22:36.314 --> 00:22:40.819
To the discontented.
rumors are feed.

245
00:22:45.323 --> 00:22:47.117
Your Grace.

246
00:22:49.202 --> 00:22:53.832
What you cannot do.
let others do for you.

247
00:22:54.958 --> 00:22:58.293
There is more than
one way to fight a war.

248
00:23:20.316 --> 00:23:22.985
The thought
of her lying in a field.

249
00:23:22.986 --> 00:23:25.864
broken amongst her enemies.

250
00:23:36.207 --> 00:23:40.420
Did your grandmother ever tell
you of the night she claimed Meleys?

251
00:23:41.421 --> 00:23:43.423
She snuck into the Dragonpit.

252
00:23:44.049 --> 00:23:46.551
She knew that place
better than any Elder.

253
00:23:47.052 --> 00:23:49.220
They say she could
see in the dark.

254
00:23:50.722 --> 00:23:52.557
My father was furious.

255
00:23:52.682 --> 00:23:54.683
His own mother's dragon.

256
00:23:54.684 --> 00:23:56.061
the fastest beast ever known.

257
00:23:56.186 --> 00:23:58.020
and she'd have none of him.

258
00:23:58.021 --> 00:24:00.523
But bent her neck to Rhaenys.

259
00:24:01.566 --> 00:24:03.735
She was fierce...

260
00:24:04.861 --> 00:24:07.072
in love and in anger.

261
00:24:09.574 --> 00:24:13.286
She did not always
care for me. but...

262
00:24:14.913 --> 00:24:19.125
for what she gave me
in the end. I'm grateful.

263
00:24:24.923 --> 00:24:28.051
I wished I had known
her when she was young.

264
00:24:33.598 --> 00:24:37.936
You are very like her in some ways.

265
00:24:40.438 --> 00:24:45.401
And with her gone... I
must rely on you. I think.

266
00:24:45.402 --> 00:24:48.070
Your Grace?

267
00:24:48.071 --> 00:24:50.824
Would you give this
to your grandsire?

268
00:25:02.252 --> 00:25:04.963
I do not wish to stand alone.

269
00:25:08.633 --> 00:25:10.427
Daemon.

270
00:25:15.181 --> 00:25:16.516
<i>Daemon.</i>

271
00:25:17.267 --> 00:25:20.145
<i>You were always the strong one.</i>

272
00:25:21.980 --> 00:25:24.816
The finest swordsman...

273
00:25:27.485 --> 00:25:30.155
the fearless dragonrider.

274
00:25:31.948 --> 00:25:35.702
<i>Your brother had
great love in his heart...</i>

275
00:25:39.873 --> 00:25:42.334
<i>but he lacked your constitution.</i>

276
00:25:43.168 --> 00:25:45.962
<i>Viserys was unsuited
for the crown...</i>

277
00:25:49.007 --> 00:25:53.053
<i>but you... Daemon. you
were made to wear it.</i>

278
00:26:13.198 --> 00:26:16.368
<i>If only you'd been born first.</i>

279
00:26:17.577 --> 00:26:20.038
My favorite son.

280
00:26:26.211 --> 00:26:29.589
Is the duck not
to your liking. Your Grace?

281
00:26:34.552 --> 00:26:38.181
There's also
goose. if you'd prefer it.

282
00:26:39.849 --> 00:26:41.725
I like the goose. myself.

283
00:26:49.943 --> 00:26:51.403
I'm not hungry.

284
00:26:51.528 --> 00:26:53.738
I was saying.
given the rather dire news

285
00:26:53.863 --> 00:26:55.699
from Rook's Rest...

286
00:26:56.533 --> 00:27:00.536
it appears the winds have shifted
and each side has suffered great loss.

287
00:27:00.537 --> 00:27:04.124
and will be unsure
of what is to follow.

288
00:27:05.250 --> 00:27:08.210
A good time. then.
for a show of strength.

289
00:27:08.211 --> 00:27:09.378
I believe Willem Blackwood

290
00:27:09.379 --> 00:27:12.048
is bringing House
Bracken to heel.

291
00:27:13.258 --> 00:27:16.636
We must ready the castle
to receive a great host.

292
00:27:18.930 --> 00:27:20.764
You seem sure of this.

293
00:27:20.765 --> 00:27:23.559
All men may be led. Ser Simon.

294
00:27:23.560 --> 00:27:25.311
Even Rivermen.

295
00:27:26.271 --> 00:27:30.275
'Tis a matter of showing them
whom it behooves them to follow.

296
00:27:31.443 --> 00:27:33.778
How does the work here progress?

297
00:27:34.112 --> 00:27:37.906
Um... we're drawing
water for the kitchens

298
00:27:37.907 --> 00:27:40.285
- and lighting the forges.
- Very well.

299
00:27:40.410 --> 00:27:42.911
That is merely the
beginning. of course.

300
00:27:42.912 --> 00:27:44.664
The roof alone
has needed tending

301
00:27:44.789 --> 00:27:45.749
since the reign of Aenys.

302
00:27:45.750 --> 00:27:46.957
And the storerooms.

303
00:27:46.958 --> 00:27:49.002
And...

304
00:27:49.127 --> 00:27:51.629
and the Wailing
Tower.

305
00:27:52.130 --> 00:27:54.632
The bats have made the
corridors almost impassable

306
00:27:54.758 --> 00:27:56.760
with the quantity of their...

307
00:27:57.802 --> 00:27:59.346
Their shit.

308
00:28:01.473 --> 00:28:03.350
I venture there are
smiths and armorers

309
00:28:03.475 --> 00:28:05.934
to be found near
Nutton and Riverbend.

310
00:28:05.935 --> 00:28:07.979
Well. send for them.
and levy the farmers

311
00:28:08.104 --> 00:28:10.106
from Antlers to High Heart.

312
00:28:10.315 --> 00:28:14.152
Task their huntsmen to
bring us meat and wood.

313
00:28:14.277 --> 00:28:16.945
Um. there is. of course.
the matter of payment.

314
00:28:18.615 --> 00:28:23.161
After the. the tragedy
that befell his father...

315
00:28:23.495 --> 00:28:29.291
Larys transferred his family's
wealth to King's Landing.

316
00:28:29.292 --> 00:28:31.711
Is there any gold
left in your coffers?

317
00:28:31.836 --> 00:28:36.508
Enough to keep this small
establishment you see fed and warm.

318
00:28:37.509 --> 00:28:39.010
Relatively.

319
00:28:41.388 --> 00:28:44.848
I... I rather thought.
Your Grace. as

320
00:28:44.849 --> 00:28:48.186
emissary to the Queen

321
00:28:48.311 --> 00:28:52.147
that p-perhaps she could
provide the necessary coin

322
00:28:52.148 --> 00:28:55.735
- if you could only write to her.
- No.

323
00:28:55.860 --> 00:28:57.862
Harrenhal is my command.

324
00:28:58.321 --> 00:29:01.199
I shall guarantee
the payment myself.

325
00:29:02.033 --> 00:29:03.827
Up. up.

326
00:29:06.871 --> 00:29:08.873
Very well. Your Grace.

327
00:29:09.207 --> 00:29:12.377
You should address
me as "my king."

328
00:29:12.711 --> 00:29:14.379
But you're the prince.

329
00:29:14.713 --> 00:29:17.048
What would you call the
husband of the queen?

330
00:29:17.173 --> 00:29:18.841
- Well. the king...
- There it is. then.

331
00:29:18.842 --> 00:29:20.385
Consort.

332
00:29:21.386 --> 00:29:24.347
That last bit seems
unnecessary. don't you think?

333
00:29:30.061 --> 00:29:32.021
The armor
was Valyrian steel.

334
00:29:32.022 --> 00:29:36.401
but His Grace suffered grievous
burns over much of his body.

335
00:29:37.360 --> 00:29:39.237
He has many broken bones.

336
00:29:39.362 --> 00:29:42.740
I fear there are
more injuries within.

337
00:29:42.741 --> 00:29:44.743
injuries we cannot see.

338
00:29:46.244 --> 00:29:48.580
We are
grateful for your works.

339
00:29:48.705 --> 00:29:49.706
Grand Maester.

340
00:29:50.790 --> 00:29:53.376
- Has he woken?
- No.

341
00:29:54.627 --> 00:29:59.299
I must admit. I'm not
sure he will ever wake.

342
00:29:59.424 --> 00:30:02.635
I have plied my crafts
to their fullest extents.

343
00:30:02.761 --> 00:30:06.931
Our king's fate lies
with the gods now.

344
00:30:17.442 --> 00:30:20.445
A king cannot rule in his sleep.

345
00:30:20.570 --> 00:30:22.947
The realm will have
noticed his absence.

346
00:30:23.448 --> 00:30:27.160
Let them hear of his
great deeds at Rook's Rest.

347
00:30:27.285 --> 00:30:29.996
But now we must name
a regent to take his place

348
00:30:30.121 --> 00:30:31.790
until he recovers...

349
00:30:34.125 --> 00:30:35.460
or does not.

350
00:30:36.961 --> 00:30:39.254
A wise strategy. Your Grace.

351
00:30:39.255 --> 00:30:40.965
A regency will assure the people

352
00:30:41.091 --> 00:30:43.635
of the stability of the crown.

353
00:30:46.179 --> 00:30:49.307
Did you have a candidate
in mind. Your Grace?

354
00:30:49.766 --> 00:30:51.486
I myself served in this
role for my husband.

355
00:30:51.601 --> 00:30:53.143
I am well-prepared
to do it again.

356
00:30:53.144 --> 00:30:54.603
You played your part admirably

357
00:30:54.604 --> 00:30:56.271
in a time of peace. Your Grace.

358
00:30:56.272 --> 00:30:58.774
but circumstances have changed.

359
00:30:58.775 --> 00:31:00.485
And here I had forgotten.

360
00:31:00.610 --> 00:31:02.778
The king
does not lack for heirs.

361
00:31:02.779 --> 00:31:07.825
The obvious choice is his
immediate successor. Prince Aemond.

362
00:31:07.826 --> 00:31:09.159
Agreed.

363
00:31:09.160 --> 00:31:11.995
Aemond is young.

364
00:31:11.996 --> 00:31:14.958
And his lack of restraint
has already cost us dearly.

365
00:31:24.175 --> 00:31:28.346
It is experience that
offers the surest path to security.

366
00:31:28.471 --> 00:31:31.473
Queen Alicent ably shouldered
the duties of the realm

367
00:31:31.474 --> 00:31:33.183
when her husband's
health failed him.

368
00:31:33.184 --> 00:31:34.518
Experience is valuable. yes.

369
00:31:34.519 --> 00:31:35.978
but the dowager
queen is a woman.

370
00:31:35.979 --> 00:31:39.232
I am no stranger to rule
or to sitting at this council.

371
00:31:39.357 --> 00:31:40.570
Aemond is a
fearsome dragonrider.

372
00:31:40.650 --> 00:31:41.984
His skill is best
employed in the field.

373
00:31:41.985 --> 00:31:44.987
but my experience is
needed here. at this table.

374
00:31:44.988 --> 00:31:47.364
No offense was meant.
Your Grace. but...

375
00:31:47.365 --> 00:31:52.537
- at a time when we must show strength.
- Lord Larys?

376
00:31:52.662 --> 00:31:55.331
I agree. Your Grace. It
must be Prince Aemond.

377
00:31:57.042 --> 00:31:59.501
What would it say if. in
response to Rhaenyra's crowning.

378
00:31:59.502 --> 00:32:01.921
we raised up a woman of our own?

379
00:32:04.716 --> 00:32:06.217
But. um...

380
00:32:07.594 --> 00:32:09.511
but the Hand speaks
for the king's voice.

381
00:32:09.512 --> 00:32:11.765
Ser Criston. what say you?

382
00:32:18.563 --> 00:32:20.940
Aemond is the next in line.

383
00:32:23.068 --> 00:32:24.611
It must be him.

384
00:32:29.115 --> 00:32:31.368
It's agreed then.

385
00:32:52.597 --> 00:32:54.933
What is our standing
in the Riverlands?

386
00:32:56.434 --> 00:32:59.061
The
banners of House Tully

387
00:32:59.062 --> 00:33:01.271
are in disarray. Your Grace.

388
00:33:01.272 --> 00:33:02.482
Prince Daemon has little hope

389
00:33:02.607 --> 00:33:05.109
of fielding an army
of any size. for now.

390
00:33:06.736 --> 00:33:08.737
We would do well
to send word to young Oscar Tully.

391
00:33:08.738 --> 00:33:10.660
It's only a matter of time

392
00:33:10.740 --> 00:33:13.117
before he inherits
his grandsire's mantle.

393
00:33:13.118 --> 00:33:15.120
Tell me. Lord Strong.

394
00:33:15.245 --> 00:33:16.663
how I can trust the
counsel of a man

395
00:33:16.788 --> 00:33:18.331
who leaves the
jewel of the Riverlands

396
00:33:18.456 --> 00:33:20.959
to be plucked by our enemy?

397
00:33:24.462 --> 00:33:25.964
Your brother's host
can meet Daemon.

398
00:33:26.089 --> 00:33:27.298
He should quicken its pace

399
00:33:27.424 --> 00:33:28.424
and check the Rivermen

400
00:33:28.425 --> 00:33:29.925
while their banners
are in disarray.

401
00:33:29.926 --> 00:33:32.178
I shall send Lord
Jason encouragement.

402
00:33:32.303 --> 00:33:35.140
- What else?
- We might turn our attention

403
00:33:35.265 --> 00:33:37.599
to the smallfolk here
in King's Landing.

404
00:33:37.600 --> 00:33:40.145
They have grown weary of
the Sea Snake's blockade.

405
00:33:40.270 --> 00:33:42.313
So have we all.

406
00:33:42.439 --> 00:33:43.568
Many
are fleeing the city.

407
00:33:43.648 --> 00:33:46.985
spreading word of
their fear and unrest.

408
00:33:47.318 --> 00:33:50.279
Then
let the gates be closed.

409
00:33:52.449 --> 00:33:55.117
No one is to leave or
enter. save with our consent.

410
00:33:55.118 --> 00:33:57.996
Merchants. so forth.

411
00:34:02.167 --> 00:34:04.127
Go to your tasks.

412
00:34:04.836 --> 00:34:07.338
We shall meet
again at first light.

413
00:34:07.339 --> 00:34:11.468
And someone cut
down the fucking ratcatchers.

414
00:34:18.350 --> 00:34:20.685
The city's safe no longer.

415
00:34:22.354 --> 00:34:23.855
There is no food.

416
00:34:24.731 --> 00:34:26.815
Our neighbors are
stealing from each other.

417
00:34:26.816 --> 00:34:28.068
We must get out.

418
00:34:28.193 --> 00:34:29.985
And where would you have us go?

419
00:34:29.986 --> 00:34:32.197
North. maybe? South?

420
00:34:32.864 --> 00:34:34.865
For all we know. every road
leads into the dragons' teeth.

421
00:34:34.866 --> 00:34:37.369
Like the one they carted
through the streets?

422
00:34:38.036 --> 00:34:42.415
You think Rhaenyra will let
such an affront go unchallenged?

423
00:34:45.335 --> 00:34:48.046
We should make for Tumbleton.

424
00:34:48.171 --> 00:34:50.090
My brother will have room.

425
00:34:50.215 --> 00:34:52.050
You would have me turn beggar?

426
00:34:58.056 --> 00:35:00.849
Are we not beggars already?

427
00:35:00.850 --> 00:35:02.560
Have you been paid
for those machines

428
00:35:02.686 --> 00:35:03.561
you were forced to build?

429
00:35:03.562 --> 00:35:05.271
The king has promised payment.

430
00:35:05.397 --> 00:35:08.400
The king has lied!

431
00:35:19.911 --> 00:35:21.746
By all means...

432
00:35:22.414 --> 00:35:25.959
stay and wait for his
empty promises. husband.

433
00:35:27.877 --> 00:35:30.922
With them. you can
feed the mouths of ghosts.

434
00:36:10.253 --> 00:36:12.255
Presumed you'd be here.

435
00:36:12.630 --> 00:36:15.300
Seeing faithfully to the
Prince Regent's commands.

436
00:36:15.842 --> 00:36:17.926
Aemond is the next in line.

437
00:36:17.927 --> 00:36:21.096
- It is the order of things.
- You know what he is...

438
00:36:21.097 --> 00:36:23.141
what he has somehow become.

439
00:36:25.810 --> 00:36:27.269
Has your loyalty faded?

440
00:36:27.270 --> 00:36:29.271
Or does it flourish
only at night

441
00:36:29.272 --> 00:36:32.150
and flee the
sunrise like a moth?

442
00:36:35.779 --> 00:36:37.321
What I saw at Rook's Rest...

443
00:36:37.322 --> 00:36:40.784
What? What did you see?

444
00:36:44.662 --> 00:36:46.831
Their armor melted.

445
00:36:48.500 --> 00:36:51.169
There were men
walking. They were on fire.

446
00:36:54.506 --> 00:36:56.841
We have given the
war to the dragons.

447
00:36:58.343 --> 00:37:00.011
A dragonrider should lead us.

448
00:37:04.349 --> 00:37:06.559
And what of justice.
of temperance?

449
00:37:06.685 --> 00:37:09.854
Or is strength now
to be our only god?

450
00:37:15.193 --> 00:37:17.195
So you cast me aside.

451
00:37:18.363 --> 00:37:20.365
Have I not spared you?

452
00:37:22.033 --> 00:37:25.995
What we must do
now is... terrible.

453
00:37:27.706 --> 00:37:29.708
Will you preside over it?

454
00:37:30.208 --> 00:37:34.170
- Is this who you are. Alicent?
- I did not ask to be spared.

455
00:37:37.549 --> 00:37:39.759
And I did not give you
leave to speak my name.

456
00:37:52.605 --> 00:37:54.523
Halt!

457
00:38:00.071 --> 00:38:01.239
Stay back!

458
00:38:02.907 --> 00:38:04.868
We've got to get out!

459
00:38:05.535 --> 00:38:07.078
Somebody get him!

460
00:38:07.746 --> 00:38:09.748
Stay back! No!

461
00:38:09.873 --> 00:38:12.083
Holdfast. holdfast!

462
00:38:12.208 --> 00:38:14.753
Stay back! Hold!

463
00:38:19.424 --> 00:38:20.759
Back!

464
00:38:21.593 --> 00:38:24.721
Disperse. disperse!

465
00:38:25.638 --> 00:38:27.932
By order of Aemond Targaryen.

466
00:38:28.058 --> 00:38:30.810
Prince Regent and
Protector of the Realm...

467
00:38:30.935 --> 00:38:33.228
- Aemond?
- Does he mean the king?

468
00:38:33.229 --> 00:38:35.773
- I don't know.
- You cannot keep us here!

469
00:38:35.774 --> 00:38:38.734
- You are ordered to return to your homes!
- We want meat!

470
00:38:38.735 --> 00:38:40.402
- Meat!
- Meat!

471
00:38:50.580 --> 00:38:52.123
Stay back!

472
00:38:59.798 --> 00:39:04.259
Our Lord Grover
Tully has not declared for Rhaenyra.

473
00:39:04.260 --> 00:39:06.595
It means death to bare
steel against your liege.

474
00:39:06.596 --> 00:39:08.973
as I'm sure my prince is aware.

475
00:39:10.475 --> 00:39:12.811
And against your queen?

476
00:39:19.484 --> 00:39:23.446
Jason Lannister
is marshaling to the west.

477
00:39:24.280 --> 00:39:26.700
We need to check him
before he reaches Riverrun.

478
00:39:27.492 --> 00:39:29.451
That requires passage.

479
00:39:29.452 --> 00:39:31.787
And if Stark's army is too slow?

480
00:39:31.788 --> 00:39:33.622
The wind's rising.

481
00:39:33.623 --> 00:39:35.332
Winter is nigh upon us.

482
00:39:35.333 --> 00:39:36.835
Our hesitance does not lie

483
00:39:36.960 --> 00:39:38.961
in Rhaenyra as Queen.

484
00:39:38.962 --> 00:39:43.340
nor in the ruminations
of Lord Tully. the oaf.

485
00:39:43.341 --> 00:39:46.135
Our fear lies in Vhagar.

486
00:39:46.136 --> 00:39:49.138
You fear a dragon leagues away

487
00:39:49.139 --> 00:39:52.058
when mine own sits
outside your walls?

488
00:39:56.146 --> 00:39:59.816
- Do you offer us your protection?
- I do.

489
00:40:06.072 --> 00:40:09.199
And the protection of my uncle.

490
00:40:09.200 --> 00:40:13.580
And Daemon. I'm sure.
has consented to this?

491
00:40:13.705 --> 00:40:15.664
He will do as his
queen commands.

492
00:40:15.665 --> 00:40:17.666
That does lend us some comfort.

493
00:40:17.667 --> 00:40:19.001
Though it occurs
to me that dragons

494
00:40:19.002 --> 00:40:22.505
- cannot be in two places at once.
- Or three.

495
00:40:25.425 --> 00:40:27.344
What do you want?

496
00:40:29.346 --> 00:40:33.265
Larys Strong has been
relieved of his castle.

497
00:40:33.266 --> 00:40:36.770
Does the queen intend
to raise up a new lord?

498
00:40:40.940 --> 00:40:42.525
You want Harrenhal.

499
00:41:01.252 --> 00:41:06.424
For that... my mother will
want more than your crossing.

500
00:41:08.051 --> 00:41:10.261
What does Her Grace desire?

501
00:41:12.764 --> 00:41:15.100
Bent knees.

502
00:42:08.820 --> 00:42:09.988
Up.

503
00:42:10.488 --> 00:42:12.281
You were
born to wield a sword.

504
00:42:12.282 --> 00:42:16.452
but not so much an axe. perhaps.

505
00:42:16.453 --> 00:42:18.162
There are
others who would sit idle

506
00:42:18.163 --> 00:42:20.330
and wait for their claims
to be brought to them.

507
00:42:20.331 --> 00:42:23.792
- That is not my way.
- Does splitting firewood justify what's followed you here?

508
00:42:23.793 --> 00:42:25.836
Let it not be said that
Daemon Targaryen

509
00:42:25.837 --> 00:42:28.130
failed to dirty his
hands in this war.

510
00:42:28.131 --> 00:42:30.300
Let me see them.

511
00:42:31.176 --> 00:42:33.219
Sit.

512
00:42:33.345 --> 00:42:34.512
Sit!

513
00:42:38.016 --> 00:42:41.310
I hear strange
things from Bracken land.

514
00:42:41.311 --> 00:42:44.689
from Stone Hedge and
Lambswold and Mory.

515
00:42:45.690 --> 00:42:47.691
There's news. then?

516
00:42:47.692 --> 00:42:49.069
News?

517
00:42:50.236 --> 00:42:51.237
No.

518
00:42:53.198 --> 00:42:55.991
What I hear. I hear in the wind.

519
00:42:55.992 --> 00:42:59.204
Cries of anguish.

520
00:43:01.039 --> 00:43:03.040
Children being taken
from their mothers.

521
00:43:03.041 --> 00:43:07.002
men coming home to
find their doors unlatched...

522
00:43:07.003 --> 00:43:09.380
their wives carried away.

523
00:43:11.508 --> 00:43:14.260
War is a terrible thing.

524
00:43:14.386 --> 00:43:16.221
This is not war.

525
00:43:16.888 --> 00:43:19.348
These are crimes
against the innocent.

526
00:43:19.349 --> 00:43:21.517
that any upright
man would repudiate.

527
00:43:21.518 --> 00:43:24.353
Surely you haven't mistaken
me for an upright man.

528
00:43:26.189 --> 00:43:29.733
The Brackens had their
chance to do as I required.

529
00:43:29.734 --> 00:43:32.027
They will perhaps think
better of their decision

530
00:43:32.028 --> 00:43:35.407
if their children's
lives are staked on it.

531
00:43:36.449 --> 00:43:39.244
Is that the kind of
army you would raise?

532
00:43:40.036 --> 00:43:42.247
Men who hate you...

533
00:43:42.747 --> 00:43:44.373
who serve you under duress?

534
00:43:44.374 --> 00:43:47.585
Well. once they agree to
serve me. I'll treat them fairly.

535
00:43:47.711 --> 00:43:48.877
Set an example for the rest

536
00:43:48.878 --> 00:43:50.922
of the Riverlands to follow.

537
00:43:51.047 --> 00:43:53.299
And once again. in
the name of power.

538
00:43:53.425 --> 00:43:56.428
it's the weak and the
women who must endure.

539
00:43:59.097 --> 00:44:02.142
That fool. Aegon.
is unlike to survive.

540
00:44:04.102 --> 00:44:06.479
The realm will suffer if
Aemond One-Eye rules.

541
00:44:07.939 --> 00:44:09.607
You should pray
you never meet him.

542
00:44:10.108 --> 00:44:12.277
He will cut you down
soon as wish you good-day.

543
00:44:12.402 --> 00:44:13.945
I'd heard the same
thing about you.

544
00:44:14.070 --> 00:44:15.070
But I'll cross you no further.

545
00:44:15.071 --> 00:44:16.614
I'm sure your
tactics are. after all.

546
00:44:16.740 --> 00:44:18.574
approved by the queen.

547
00:44:23.997 --> 00:44:26.416
She cannot succeed. Alys.

548
00:44:26.958 --> 00:44:29.084
Even if I willed it to be so.

549
00:44:29.085 --> 00:44:31.129
The people who support
her will not be led by her.

550
00:44:31.254 --> 00:44:33.255
They look to a man for strength.

551
00:44:33.256 --> 00:44:34.341
Who's better suited to it?

552
00:44:34.466 --> 00:44:36.925
The Hightowers
with their scheming?

553
00:44:36.926 --> 00:44:39.346
Or Viserys's first true heir?

554
00:44:40.305 --> 00:44:42.806
When I take King's Landing...

555
00:44:42.807 --> 00:44:44.266
Rhaenyra is welcome
to join me there

556
00:44:44.267 --> 00:44:46.811
and take her place by my side.

557
00:44:46.936 --> 00:44:50.940
King and queen...
ruling together.

558
00:44:51.441 --> 00:44:54.151
- And if you lose?
- Then I'll be dead.

559
00:44:54.152 --> 00:44:56.445
and none of this
will be my problem.

560
00:44:56.446 --> 00:44:59.824
It's a pity. don't you think. that
you never knew your mother?

561
00:45:03.328 --> 00:45:05.663
A message. Your Grace.

562
00:45:10.543 --> 00:45:13.380
fresh news from Stone Hedge.

563
00:45:13.505 --> 00:45:15.631
The Blackwoods have
overwhelmed the Brackens.

564
00:45:15.632 --> 00:45:19.344
and. Lord Amos has
pledged his banner to you.

565
00:45:19.678 --> 00:45:21.846
House Bracken is yours.

566
00:45:23.014 --> 00:45:25.975
Call Ser Willem here so
that I might congratulate him.

567
00:45:26.309 --> 00:45:29.187
The Blackwoods will
be feted in these halls.

568
00:45:40.365 --> 00:45:42.534
I sought you at High Tide.

569
00:45:43.159 --> 00:45:45.537
I was surprised when
they said you were here.

570
00:45:46.705 --> 00:45:48.707
My castle is a tomb.

571
00:45:49.916 --> 00:45:52.085
Empty. Haunted.

572
00:45:52.752 --> 00:45:56.089
I am sad to have
missed its highest days.

573
00:45:56.881 --> 00:45:58.173
I imagine your Hall of Nine

574
00:45:58.174 --> 00:46:00.509
filled with lords and kings.

575
00:46:00.510 --> 00:46:03.763
all eager to treat with the
legendary Lord of the Tides.

576
00:46:05.515 --> 00:46:06.682
The wealth you brought back

577
00:46:06.683 --> 00:46:08.017
from Yi Ti and Asshai.

578
00:46:08.018 --> 00:46:11.396
inspiring awe and envy.

579
00:46:13.565 --> 00:46:15.775
I wonder if any of them
knew it was all for her.

580
00:46:24.743 --> 00:46:27.120
Queen Rhaenyra
wishes to name you Hand.

581
00:46:30.457 --> 00:46:34.586
Even the death of my
wife does not content her.

582
00:46:36.588 --> 00:46:38.965
Has she not asked
enough of my house?

583
00:46:39.424 --> 00:46:42.260
It is a sign of
her great esteem.

584
00:46:43.219 --> 00:46:45.139
Or does she think the
position will compensate me

585
00:46:45.263 --> 00:46:47.556
for my loss?

586
00:46:47.557 --> 00:46:50.059
Pledge your peace to
King's Landing. then.

587
00:46:50.060 --> 00:46:52.479
They will accept
it most gleefully.

588
00:46:54.773 --> 00:46:57.734
Rather I would sail into
the West and be lost.

589
00:46:58.818 --> 00:47:00.612
You have done so before.

590
00:47:00.737 --> 00:47:03.656
at great cost to yourself
and those who loved you.

591
00:47:06.117 --> 00:47:09.329
Rhaenys was not
only your wife...

592
00:47:09.454 --> 00:47:11.915
not a thing to be
taken from you.

593
00:47:12.582 --> 00:47:15.960
She was a Targaryen princess.

594
00:47:16.086 --> 00:47:17.294
The Queen Who Never Was.

595
00:47:17.295 --> 00:47:20.089
And she flew to Rook's
Rest of her own will.

596
00:47:20.090 --> 00:47:22.424
- In defense of her kin.
- And she died.

597
00:47:22.425 --> 00:47:24.761
She died as she would
have wished to die...

598
00:47:25.303 --> 00:47:28.473
with honor. in dragonfire.

599
00:47:28.973 --> 00:47:30.433
The way my mother chose...

600
00:47:32.477 --> 00:47:35.480
and the way I myself
wish to meet my end.

601
00:47:42.487 --> 00:47:45.781
I grieve my grandmother
who loved me

602
00:47:45.782 --> 00:47:47.992
but I carry her on with me.

603
00:47:49.035 --> 00:47:53.665
I will see Rhaenyra ascend the
Iron Throne. as Rhaenys wished.

604
00:47:54.165 --> 00:47:56.334
As Rhaenys herself should have.

605
00:47:58.795 --> 00:48:01.673
You yourself may
do as you see fit.

606
00:48:05.176 --> 00:48:06.802
Granddaughter.

607
00:48:14.185 --> 00:48:17.522
I would make you my heir.

608
00:48:18.982 --> 00:48:20.984
I am blood and fire.

609
00:48:21.401 --> 00:48:24.654
Driftmark must
pass to salt and sea.

610
00:48:43.214 --> 00:48:44.591
Your Grace.

611
00:48:48.178 --> 00:48:49.596
You were correct...

612
00:48:50.889 --> 00:48:53.850
in saying our best hope
of an army is with Daemon.

613
00:48:56.186 --> 00:49:01.900
And I have. perhaps. erred in
waiting for him to prove himself.

614
00:49:03.902 --> 00:49:05.904
I wish you to go to Harrenhal.

615
00:49:07.572 --> 00:49:10.241
Are you removing
me from your council?

616
00:49:11.743 --> 00:49:13.078
Ser Alfred...

617
00:49:13.787 --> 00:49:17.414
I-I-I will not deny you have
tried my patience of late.

618
00:49:17.415 --> 00:49:19.584
or that I would prefer a council

619
00:49:19.709 --> 00:49:21.252
more inclined to
champion their queen.

620
00:49:21.378 --> 00:49:24.046
but...

621
00:49:24.047 --> 00:49:27.383
you and your house
served my father well.

622
00:49:27.384 --> 00:49:30.637
and I know you will never
accept the Hightower claim.

623
00:49:32.138 --> 00:49:34.891
Not while I live. Your Grace.

624
00:49:37.560 --> 00:49:41.230
We cannot challenge King's
Landing without the Riverlands

625
00:49:41.231 --> 00:49:45.402
but I will not send a message
by raven for Daemon to disregard.

626
00:49:47.445 --> 00:49:53.493
I ask you to... reason with him.

627
00:49:53.618 --> 00:49:58.456
Find out his state of
mind and his intentions.

628
00:50:00.166 --> 00:50:01.751
Intentions?

629
00:50:02.627 --> 00:50:06.423
Whether he means to raise
a host for me or for himself.

630
00:50:09.259 --> 00:50:10.468
He would not dare.

631
00:50:10.593 --> 00:50:13.471
Have you known
Daemon to lack in daring?

632
00:50:14.973 --> 00:50:16.516
Go now with haste.

633
00:50:16.641 --> 00:50:19.477
I'll send good men
to see to your safety.

634
00:50:26.985 --> 00:50:29.654
Have you any message for him?

635
00:50:33.283 --> 00:50:36.828
Tell him I would much like
to finish our last conversation.

636
00:50:39.205 --> 00:50:40.623
Your Grace.

637
00:51:16.701 --> 00:51:18.411
Your Grace.

638
00:51:21.873 --> 00:51:26.211
What is it. Ser Simon? Is
the pudding now served?

639
00:51:26.753 --> 00:51:29.255
The Riverlords have
come. Your Grace.

640
00:51:29.381 --> 00:51:32.217
- They wish an audience.
- Now?

641
00:51:32.717 --> 00:51:35.220
- What godless hour is it?
- The wolf.

642
00:51:35.845 --> 00:51:37.889
They are demanding
to speak presently.

643
00:52:08.753 --> 00:52:12.132
I see I must begin here
with a lesson in etiquette.

644
00:52:12.257 --> 00:52:13.382
Or failing that. in proper fear

645
00:52:13.383 --> 00:52:15.593
of your Targaryen master.

646
00:52:17.095 --> 00:52:21.599
Is there some reason you feel
free to wake a king in his bed?

647
00:52:22.308 --> 00:52:24.893
Or shall I now begin
your education?

648
00:52:24.894 --> 00:52:26.228
House Bracken

649
00:52:26.229 --> 00:52:29.983
have been brought to heel at
the hands of Willem Blackwood.

650
00:52:30.108 --> 00:52:33.444
- That news is stale.
- Yes.

651
00:52:33.445 --> 00:52:35.404
There have been.
um. complications.

652
00:52:35.405 --> 00:52:37.906
The sacred septs
on Bracken lands

653
00:52:37.907 --> 00:52:41.327
- were looted and burned.
- As were the fields and farms.

654
00:52:41.453 --> 00:52:42.787
The livestock was stolen

655
00:52:42.912 --> 00:52:44.455
and our peasants
put to the sword.

656
00:52:44.456 --> 00:52:47.125
They pursued the
women and the children.

657
00:52:47.250 --> 00:52:48.584
There were works of barbarity.

658
00:52:48.585 --> 00:52:52.339
Punishing Bracken for his
own treasons is one thing. aye.

659
00:52:52.464 --> 00:52:55.133
- But these other acts.
- The Brackens were given their chance.

660
00:52:55.258 --> 00:52:57.760
- They would not see reason.
- The Blackwoods have exploited

661
00:52:57.761 --> 00:52:59.595
the war for the
crown to visit atrocities

662
00:52:59.596 --> 00:53:02.139
- upon their old rivals.
- I have seen my fair share of their quarrels.

663
00:53:02.140 --> 00:53:03.728
and I tell you. there
is no honor in a fight

664
00:53:03.808 --> 00:53:05.768
- such as this.
- Honor? What of common decency?

665
00:53:05.769 --> 00:53:08.146
These beasts proudly carried

666
00:53:08.271 --> 00:53:10.023
the banner of House Targaryen.

667
00:53:10.148 --> 00:53:11.983
Red dragon on black.

668
00:53:18.323 --> 00:53:21.826
A terrible war
is being fought in these lands.

669
00:53:25.038 --> 00:53:27.290
Have you looked after our girls?

670
00:53:34.673 --> 00:53:36.713
We should've expected
nothing more from a man

671
00:53:36.800 --> 00:53:38.718
who ordered the
slaughter of a child

672
00:53:38.843 --> 00:53:40.553
in his mother's arms.

673
00:53:42.347 --> 00:53:45.725
That is a lie. And I will have the
man who told it brought before me.

674
00:53:45.850 --> 00:53:50.689
Well. your man is half
the kingdom. my prince.

675
00:53:53.525 --> 00:53:55.527
Know this. interloper:

676
00:53:56.027 --> 00:53:58.863
the Riverlands are
an ancient place.

677
00:53:58.988 --> 00:54:02.701
watched closely by the
eyes of old gods and new.

678
00:54:03.076 --> 00:54:04.744
And dragon or no.

679
00:54:04.869 --> 00:54:08.206
we shall not raise our
banners for a tyrant.

680
00:55:16.066 --> 00:55:20.111
- Move along. lass.
- I have an errand... for the lady Mysaria.

681
00:55:21.279 --> 00:55:22.447
I thought she was dead.

682
00:55:23.239 --> 00:55:25.784
Would she die without
collecting her due?

683
00:55:27.285 --> 00:55:29.162
I must see an old friend.

684
00:55:30.789 --> 00:55:32.957
Most people want out these days.

685
00:56:18.211 --> 00:56:19.211
Elinda.

686
00:57:10.889 --> 00:57:13.099
Was it worth the price?

687
00:58:03.942 --> 00:58:05.902
Mummy.

688
00:58:22.794 --> 00:58:24.337
Prince Jacaerys. Your Grace.

689
00:58:49.154 --> 00:58:50.488
Visenya.

690
00:58:51.322 --> 00:58:57.037
Vhagar's first rider. and the
first wielder of Dark Sister.

691
00:58:58.496 --> 00:59:00.956
I hope you do not mean
to use her as an example.

692
00:59:00.957 --> 00:59:02.666
Why shouldn't I?

693
00:59:02.667 --> 00:59:05.045
W... It was a long time ago.

694
00:59:15.138 --> 00:59:17.515
What is the mood at the Twins?

695
00:59:19.017 --> 00:59:21.353
Did his lordship quibble?

696
00:59:23.521 --> 00:59:27.484
He wishes for the Freys
to be granted Harrenhal.

697
00:59:28.860 --> 00:59:31.196
At war's end. Assuming.

698
00:59:33.865 --> 00:59:35.408
I'm proud of you. Jace.

699
00:59:35.533 --> 00:59:38.036
You have done our
cause a great service.

700
00:59:40.246 --> 00:59:43.249
Then. why do you look angry?

701
00:59:51.341 --> 00:59:54.343
You chafed at being
prevented from action.

702
00:59:54.344 --> 00:59:57.179
Imagine my lot. I'm
a dragonrider as well.

703
00:59:57.180 --> 01:00:00.225
with a war being fought
over my ascension.

704
01:00:01.226 --> 01:00:03.395
And yet. I must wait here...

705
01:00:04.396 --> 01:00:06.689
always prudent...

706
01:00:06.690 --> 01:00:08.065
sending others to fight

707
01:00:08.066 --> 01:00:10.527
and be felled in my name.

708
01:00:10.902 --> 01:00:13.279
Even you have
managed to do your part.

709
01:00:13.863 --> 01:00:15.573
You are the queen...

710
01:00:15.949 --> 01:00:17.199
the tie that binds us.

711
01:00:17.200 --> 01:00:18.955
- No harm can come to you.
- And you are my son.

712
01:00:19.035 --> 01:00:21.246
and I did not give
you leave to go.

713
01:00:23.081 --> 01:00:25.792
You do not give me
leave to go to anything.

714
01:00:26.126 --> 01:00:27.376
But who else is there?
Rhaenys is dead.

715
01:00:27.377 --> 01:00:29.253
and Baela cannot
bear the burden alone.

716
01:00:29.254 --> 01:00:31.922
And when Aemond
comes hunting for you?

717
01:00:31.923 --> 01:00:34.258
Your dragon is young.

718
01:00:34.259 --> 01:00:36.553
Will you fly before
Vhagar as Luke did?

719
01:00:43.268 --> 01:00:45.395
Perhaps Daemon could...

720
01:00:48.773 --> 01:00:50.608
Daemon is not here.

721
01:00:51.317 --> 01:00:54.903
And Aemond now
rules in King's Landing.

722
01:00:54.904 --> 01:00:59.241
- Is Aegon dead?
- Dead or alive. we have no answer for Vhagar.

723
01:00:59.242 --> 01:01:02.620
Aemond will not wait long to
press his advantage. And then what?

724
01:01:05.081 --> 01:01:06.791
I have done all I can from here.

725
01:01:06.916 --> 01:01:09.626
sent my messages.
invoked my alliances.

726
01:01:09.627 --> 01:01:12.255
But if all else fails.
it is I who must fight.

727
01:01:13.965 --> 01:01:16.759
Vhagar is big. but
Syrax is quicker.

728
01:01:16.760 --> 01:01:21.514
- So was Meleys.
- Meleys fought two dragons and one of them is slain.

729
01:01:23.099 --> 01:01:24.354
Shall I fight for my birthright?

730
01:01:24.434 --> 01:01:27.312
Or shall I wait here until
we are all destroyed?

731
01:01:32.984 --> 01:01:35.153
I need dragons.

732
01:01:38.323 --> 01:01:41.493
We have no dearth of dragons.

733
01:01:42.160 --> 01:01:45.162
We have two large enough
to stand against Vhagar.

734
01:01:45.163 --> 01:01:48.457
They are called
Vermithor and Silverwing

735
01:01:48.458 --> 01:01:50.001
and they sleep just
beneath our feet.

736
01:01:50.126 --> 01:01:51.210
Yes. and if only
they had riders.

737
01:01:51.211 --> 01:01:53.505
none could stand against me.

738
01:01:54.130 --> 01:01:57.509
I would go forth in strength
and not from necessity.

739
01:01:58.802 --> 01:02:00.053
There is Rhaena.

740
01:02:00.178 --> 01:02:03.348
Who nearly lost
her life in her last attempt.

741
01:02:04.724 --> 01:02:06.726
I would not risk it again.

742
01:02:12.524 --> 01:02:15.694
There are those of our
line who never ruled.

743
01:02:16.361 --> 01:02:19.906
Those who married
into other noble houses.

744
01:02:20.031 --> 01:02:22.658
their children born
with other names.

745
01:02:22.659 --> 01:02:26.495
A generation ago. or more.
Their blood would be thin.

746
01:02:26.496 --> 01:02:27.872
And yet...

747
01:02:28.998 --> 01:02:33.335
A dragon will only accept a
dragonlord to ride it.

748
01:02:33.336 --> 01:02:37.339
- Or so say the histories.
- Valyrian histories.

749
01:02:37.340 --> 01:02:39.508
Written to gild us in glory.

750
01:02:42.220 --> 01:02:45.015
Are you suggesting we
put a Mallister on a dragon?

751
01:02:45.432 --> 01:02:49.227
- A Tarly?
- It's better than death and defeat.

752
01:02:55.025 --> 01:02:58.360
There are records
here. surely. of our line

753
01:02:58.361 --> 01:03:00.739
and of those who fell out of it.

754
01:03:08.204 --> 01:03:09.872
There could be scores of them.

755
01:03:17.589 --> 01:03:19.466
It's a mad thought.

756
01:04:52.684 --> 01:04:54.272
<i>It
has never been attempted before.</i>

757
01:04:56.396 --> 01:04:57.564
To claim a dragon.

758
01:04:57.981 --> 01:05:00.567
<i>you must also be
prepared to die.</i>

759
01:05:01.526 --> 01:05:03.194
<i>Perhaps the gods will favor us.</i>

760
01:05:04.988 --> 01:05:06.655
<i>If Daemon
prevails in the Riverlands.</i>

761
01:05:06.656 --> 01:05:08.658
<i>I no longer have the
numbers to challenge him.</i>

762
01:05:08.992 --> 01:05:11.202
My uncle is a
challenge I welcome.

763
01:05:11.327 --> 01:05:12.327
<i>if he dares face me.</i>

764
01:05:12.537 --> 01:05:14.537
<i>You
have the arrogance of youth.</i>

765
01:05:15.373 --> 01:05:16.874
Have the indignities
of your childhood

766
01:05:16.875 --> 01:05:18.209
not yet sufficiently
been avenged?

767
01:05:19.544 --> 01:05:22.338
<i>You must see in me
a ruler and the symbols of authority.</i>

768
01:05:22.339 --> 01:05:24.090
<i>The shield and the sword.</i>

769
01:05:24.215 --> 01:05:25.716
<i>We will still never match</i>

770
01:05:25.717 --> 01:05:27.217
<i>the strength of
the Green armies.</i>

771
01:05:27.218 --> 01:05:28.345
We need Daemon.

772
01:05:29.220 --> 01:05:31.890
<i>I must now
proceed as if I stand alone.</i>

773
01:05:33.183 --> 01:05:35.517
It is my fault that you
have forgotten to fear me.

774
01:05:54.788 --> 01:05:57.081
<i>This
episode is very much</i>

775
01:05:57.082 --> 01:05:59.125
everybody vying for power.

776
01:05:59.250 --> 01:06:03.045
<i>but also. it's very much about
that happening through grief.</i>

777
01:06:06.091 --> 01:06:08.926
Much of episode five revolves
around how Rhaenys' death

778
01:06:08.927 --> 01:06:11.595
is resonating across all
of the different characters.

779
01:06:11.596 --> 01:06:15.308
<i>and no one as much as it
lands with her husband. Corlys.</i>

780
01:06:16.601 --> 01:06:19.061
<i>This poor guy. over the
course of these two seasons.</i>

781
01:06:19.062 --> 01:06:21.314
<i>has slowly had every
human connection</i>

782
01:06:21.439 --> 01:06:23.608
<i>stripped away from
him. one by one.</i>

783
01:06:23.942 --> 01:06:25.609
He's sitting in
the Hall of Nine.

784
01:06:25.610 --> 01:06:26.985
but it means nothing
to him anymore

785
01:06:26.986 --> 01:06:28.112
because she's gone.

786
01:06:28.113 --> 01:06:29.905
<i>And all of this
stuff. who cares?</i>

787
01:06:29.906 --> 01:06:31.949
<i>Steve is
an incredible actor.</i>

788
01:06:31.950 --> 01:06:36.329
He has such deep soul
to all of his performances.

789
01:06:37.163 --> 01:06:40.165
<i>I had no clue that he
was gonna have this tear.</i>

790
01:06:40.166 --> 01:06:42.168
<i>like this silent tear.
roll down his face.</i>

791
01:06:42.293 --> 01:06:44.963
It was incredibly
moving to see it.

792
01:06:47.590 --> 01:06:49.676
Our
largest dragon has been killed.

793
01:06:50.260 --> 01:06:53.137
Duskendale and
Rook's Rest are gone.

794
01:06:53.138 --> 01:06:54.263
I think everybody's reeling.

795
01:06:54.264 --> 01:06:55.864
I mean. Rhaenyra.
not the least of which.

796
01:06:55.974 --> 01:06:58.308
<i>And you hear a
lot of this backbiting</i>

797
01:06:58.309 --> 01:06:59.686
<i>and bickering
going on at the table</i>

798
01:06:59.811 --> 01:07:02.521
<i>because everybody is under a
tremendous amount of stress.</i>

799
01:07:02.522 --> 01:07:03.857
<i>They don't know how to react.</i>

800
01:07:04.441 --> 01:07:06.151
<i>But Rhaenyra
finds herself at sea.</i>

801
01:07:06.317 --> 01:07:09.863
I mean. that was her
last great female advisor.

802
01:07:10.196 --> 01:07:12.990
<i>And that's also
when Rhaenyra sees</i>

803
01:07:12.991 --> 01:07:15.034
<i>this huge power vacuum</i>

804
01:07:15.035 --> 01:07:16.536
and knows she's
got to do something.

805
01:07:17.203 --> 01:07:19.205
Queen Rhaenyra
wishes to name you Hand.

806
01:07:19.664 --> 01:07:22.709
Even the death of my
wife does not content her.

807
01:07:23.043 --> 01:07:24.960
She's playing the role of
the great politician here.

808
01:07:24.961 --> 01:07:27.047
The next best thing. next
to having Daemon back.

809
01:07:27.172 --> 01:07:29.465
<i>is one of the most
respected men in Westeros.</i>

810
01:07:29.466 --> 01:07:30.675
<i>and that's the Sea Snake.</i>

811
01:07:30.967 --> 01:07:33.510
And she doesn't exploit
Rhaenys' death to do it.

812
01:07:33.511 --> 01:07:35.846
<i>She knows that the man is
there. looking for purpose.</i>

813
01:07:35.847 --> 01:07:37.269
<i>probably looking for
a bit of vengeance.</i>

814
01:07:37.349 --> 01:07:39.183
<i>and she probably takes
advantage of that in the moment</i>

815
01:07:39.184 --> 01:07:40.685
to try to get him back on side.

816
01:07:42.812 --> 01:07:44.397
The path I walk
has never been trod.

817
01:07:44.564 --> 01:07:48.526
What you cannot do.
let others do for you.

818
01:07:49.069 --> 01:07:51.696
There is more than
one way to fight a war.

819
01:07:52.238 --> 01:07:55.240
I think Mysaria's power
increases in Rhaenys' absence

820
01:07:55.241 --> 01:07:56.700
because I think
Rhaenyra is desperate

821
01:07:56.701 --> 01:07:59.746
<i>and looking for that sympathetic
female voice in her life.</i>

822
01:08:00.246 --> 01:08:02.039
<i>Mysaria's offering
another way. which is.</i>

823
01:08:02.040 --> 01:08:03.917
"I understand the
will of the people.

824
01:08:04.084 --> 01:08:05.876
and we can manipulate that

825
01:08:05.877 --> 01:08:07.336
and play that to
your advantage."

826
01:08:07.337 --> 01:08:09.422
An element of
what we're watching

827
01:08:09.547 --> 01:08:10.714
is propaganda war.

828
01:08:10.715 --> 01:08:12.384
<i>How to win the
hearts of the people.</i>

829
01:08:12.509 --> 01:08:15.219
And that's all learning that
she receives from Mysaria.

830
01:08:15.220 --> 01:08:17.680
<i>I don't think
this is something that Rhaenyra</i>

831
01:08:17.681 --> 01:08:18.801
<i>had thought of or considered</i>

832
01:08:18.890 --> 01:08:20.725
<i>until Mysaria
brought it to the fore.</i>

833
01:08:21.017 --> 01:08:22.602
And it's a bit of a
modern concept.

834
01:08:22.727 --> 01:08:25.396
this idea of the. quote-unquote.
"power of the people."

835
01:08:25.397 --> 01:08:27.941
I have an errand
for the Lady Mysaria.

836
01:08:28.108 --> 01:08:30.234
<i>In real history.
smart and sometimes cunning</i>

837
01:08:30.235 --> 01:08:34.196
<i>and ruthless medieval sovereigns
did use people and their will</i>

838
01:08:34.197 --> 01:08:35.447
<i>to their advantage.</i>

839
01:08:35.448 --> 01:08:36.700
Behold!

840
01:08:37.200 --> 01:08:39.953
The traitor dragon. Meleys!

841
01:08:40.453 --> 01:08:42.414
It is.
Look. they've killed a dragon.

842
01:08:42.622 --> 01:08:45.083
Mark
my words. this is a black omen.

843
01:08:45.208 --> 01:08:47.209
I think this is very...
this is very Cole.

844
01:08:47.210 --> 01:08:49.086
<i>His
expectations are so high.</i>

845
01:08:49.087 --> 01:08:51.798
His expectations are
for people to honor him

846
01:08:51.923 --> 01:08:53.758
and put him up on a pedestal.

847
01:08:53.925 --> 01:08:55.259
If you look like you've won

848
01:08:55.260 --> 01:08:57.261
and you carry yourselves
like you've won.

849
01:08:57.262 --> 01:08:59.221
<i>and the public don't know
what's really happened.</i>

850
01:08:59.222 --> 01:09:00.982
<i>then that's what
everyone's going to believe.</i>

851
01:09:01.099 --> 01:09:02.976
But what happens
is so different.

852
01:09:03.101 --> 01:09:04.894
Don't they realize
we won the battle?

853
01:09:05.437 --> 01:09:07.646
Strange victory. if it was one.

854
01:09:07.647 --> 01:09:09.440
<i>The calculation
that he doesn't make</i>

855
01:09:09.441 --> 01:09:11.150
is how it will land
on the small folk.

856
01:09:11.151 --> 01:09:13.153
I mean. Meleys is
a beloved dragon

857
01:09:13.278 --> 01:09:15.279
<i>that probably flew over
that city hundreds of times</i>

858
01:09:15.280 --> 01:09:17.072
<i>and is seen as one
of these symbols</i>

859
01:09:17.073 --> 01:09:18.490
<i>of the unshakableness.</i>

860
01:09:18.491 --> 01:09:20.994
<i>of the invincibility
of the Targaryens.</i>

861
01:09:21.119 --> 01:09:22.453
I thought the dragons was gods.

862
01:09:22.454 --> 01:09:23.787
<i>You know.
as soon as people can see</i>

863
01:09:23.788 --> 01:09:26.332
you can kill dragons. well.
then anybody can do it.

864
01:09:26.458 --> 01:09:28.960
And that... does that mean
that these people that have...

865
01:09:29.085 --> 01:09:30.586
we've always thought
of as being gods

866
01:09:30.587 --> 01:09:32.672
<i>because of their
ability to ride dragons</i>

867
01:09:33.131 --> 01:09:35.592
<i>is actually all a
bit of a mirage?</i>

868
01:09:36.634 --> 01:09:39.012
<i>This is. at
best. a terrible omen</i>

869
01:09:39.137 --> 01:09:41.639
and at worst. a harbinger
of the things to come.

870
01:09:45.977 --> 01:09:48.771
The King. Ser Criston.
what befell him?

871
01:09:48.772 --> 01:09:50.357
His Grace fought valiantly.

872
01:09:51.024 --> 01:09:53.651
And Aemond? What
was his part in this?

873
01:09:53.777 --> 01:09:54.986
I could not say.

874
01:09:55.362 --> 01:09:58.698
<i>The dramatic tension
that looms over the episode is.</i>

875
01:09:58.823 --> 01:10:00.366
what is the state of Aegon?

876
01:10:00.367 --> 01:10:03.995
<i>And did he survive
the end of episode four?</i>

877
01:10:04.496 --> 01:10:06.536
<i>And will he survive through
the end of this episode?</i>

878
01:10:06.623 --> 01:10:08.123
<i>And I think that's
what's kind of looming</i>

879
01:10:08.124 --> 01:10:10.043
<i>over all these characters.
that big question.</i>

880
01:10:10.335 --> 01:10:13.129
<i>to show the cost of
letting your sovereign</i>

881
01:10:13.296 --> 01:10:15.048
get on his dragon
and ride into battle.

882
01:10:15.215 --> 01:10:17.216
Someone will have
to rule in his stead.

883
01:10:17.217 --> 01:10:19.009
<i>I mean.
it's everything he ever wanted.</i>

884
01:10:19.010 --> 01:10:21.136
With great power comes
great responsibility.

885
01:10:21.137 --> 01:10:22.889
and he's got to be
seen as someone

886
01:10:23.014 --> 01:10:24.182
<i>who knows how to wield it.</i>

887
01:10:24.391 --> 01:10:26.684
I agree. Your Grace. It
must be Prince Aemond.

888
01:10:26.685 --> 01:10:28.352
<i>I mean. this is
a massive power shift.</i>

889
01:10:28.353 --> 01:10:29.853
all of a sudden. at
the Green Council.

890
01:10:29.854 --> 01:10:33.023
It was dramatized by the meeting
where Aemond takes power

891
01:10:33.024 --> 01:10:34.264
<i>in this very kind of banal way.</i>

892
01:10:34.401 --> 01:10:36.402
<i>where he just stands up
from the foot of the table.</i>

893
01:10:36.403 --> 01:10:38.153
<i>takes his ball. and moves
over to the King's seat.</i>

894
01:10:38.154 --> 01:10:39.531
<i>and puts it down. and sits.</i>

895
01:10:39.656 --> 01:10:41.198
<i>and then starts
doling out orders</i>

896
01:10:41.199 --> 01:10:42.866
<i>while everybody.
including Alicent.</i>

897
01:10:42.867 --> 01:10:43.909
<i>especially Alicent.</i>

898
01:10:43.910 --> 01:10:45.870
<i>are reeling from the decision.</i>

899
01:10:45.995 --> 01:10:47.371
And you feel the
shift in that way

900
01:10:47.372 --> 01:10:49.748
and how different the
Red Keep is going to be

901
01:10:49.749 --> 01:10:52.168
with Aemond in charge versus
the way it was with Aegon.

902
01:10:52.544 --> 01:10:54.921
Someone cut down
the fucking ratcatchers.

903
01:10:56.506 --> 01:10:58.007
Our
terms are simple. Lord Bracken.

904
01:10:58.008 --> 01:11:00.760
Renounce the false
King Aegon as a usurper.

905
01:11:01.845 --> 01:11:03.179
Bend the knee to me.

906
01:11:04.597 --> 01:11:05.890
or your house burns.

907
01:11:06.391 --> 01:11:09.059
Daemon approaches life
always trying to hammer

908
01:11:09.060 --> 01:11:11.228
that square peg
into the round hole.

909
01:11:11.229 --> 01:11:14.858
and he's just trying to
force his will upon this place.

910
01:11:15.567 --> 01:11:18.902
I love the image of him in
his full dragon battle armor.

911
01:11:18.903 --> 01:11:19.946
sitting on the rock.

912
01:11:20.280 --> 01:11:22.740
<i>and not understanding
what's happened. and saying...</i>

913
01:11:22.741 --> 01:11:25.367
I did not think they
would be so eager to die.

914
01:11:25.368 --> 01:11:28.288
And the Riverlands is just
this unwrangleable place to him.

915
01:11:28.413 --> 01:11:30.080
<i>He's brought his values</i>

916
01:11:30.081 --> 01:11:32.792
<i>and sort of Targaryen
dragon lord values</i>

917
01:11:32.917 --> 01:11:34.126
<i>into a place that is rich</i>

918
01:11:34.127 --> 01:11:35.753
<i>with the old gods
and these old ways.</i>

919
01:11:35.754 --> 01:11:38.380
These people just don't
respect the dragon lords

920
01:11:38.381 --> 01:11:40.592
<i>the way Daemon
is hoping or used to.</i>

921
01:11:40.717 --> 01:11:43.261
I see I must begin here
with a lesson in etiquette.

922
01:11:43.428 --> 01:11:46.889
On the page. I thought.
"Yeah. this is the right territory.

923
01:11:46.890 --> 01:11:49.224
This is where we should be.
This is where his head's at."

924
01:11:49.225 --> 01:11:51.560
<i>It's how mental
his kind of state is.</i>

925
01:11:51.561 --> 01:11:54.480
<i>Is Daemon
trying to usurp Rhaenyra?</i>

926
01:11:54.481 --> 01:11:57.650
It's. like. unfair that he
wasn't given the crown.

927
01:11:57.776 --> 01:12:00.110
that he isn't listened to.

928
01:12:00.111 --> 01:12:01.988
<i>that he doesn't have that power.</i>

929
01:12:02.155 --> 01:12:03.947
We just don't know
what he's going to do

930
01:12:03.948 --> 01:12:06.325
or. ultimately. how
he's going to turn.

931
01:12:06.326 --> 01:12:08.786
<i>And while I don't think that
anybody could ever be asked</i>

932
01:12:08.787 --> 01:12:11.288
<i>to believe that he would
turn against Rhaenyra</i>

933
01:12:11.289 --> 01:12:12.791
<i>and. like. go to
war against her.</i>

934
01:12:12.957 --> 01:12:15.213
I think we could all believe
that maybe Daemon would just go

935
01:12:15.293 --> 01:12:17.127
and claim the throne for himself

936
01:12:17.128 --> 01:12:18.254
and then see what happens.

937
01:12:18.463 --> 01:12:20.340
What would you call the husband
of the Queen?

938
01:12:20.507 --> 01:12:22.591
- Well. the King...
- There it is. then.

939
01:12:22.592 --> 01:12:23.635
Consort.

940
01:12:25.178 --> 01:12:27.514
That last bit seems unnecessary.
don't you think?

941
